Dr Akinwumi Adesina, the President of African Development Bank (AfDB), has said the life of former president Olusegun Obasanjo is full of unrelenting service to humanity. Adesina stated this in a birthday message to Obasanjo as he would turn 83 on March 5, a copy which was made available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Sunday. He said Obasanjo had been making sacrifices for the noblest ideals and selflessness in nation-building. “Your every moment is spent not on yourself, but on others, always with a palpable and admirable commitment to progress, peace and stability across Africa and the world. Adamawa: FG presents relief materials to victims of Garkida… We shouldn’t politicise insecurity ― Uzodinma Buhari’s silence on Coronavirus worrying ― PDP Coronavirus: FCT residents decry scarcity of face masks ALSO READ: We shouldn’t politicise insecurity ― Uzodinma “You are the Baba for Africa. You are the Baba of Africa to the world. And I am always so very proud to call you my own Baba! Africa and the world need more of you every day, as you are a shining example. “Today you celebrate another life milestone on your 83rd Birthday. On behalf of my wife, Yemisi, and myself, I wish you a very happy, memorable and joyous birthday celebration. “I celebrate you for your outstanding leadership, for Nigeria, Africa and the world. Yours is a voice that inspires, boldly sending forth with courage, words of wisdom across the world, while inspiring hope for the future,” he said. Adesina prayed God to continue to grant Obasanjo good health, joy, peace and long life to enjoy to the fullest, the fruits of his hard work and labour of love for millions around the world. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! HERE IS HOW OVER 5000  NIGERIA MEN HAVE PERMANENTLY OVERCOME TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS RECENT DISCOVERY BY MEDICAL CONSULTANTS LOOK!  YOU DONT NEED